{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17409789","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17409789"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T05:04:08+09:30","options":[3],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T05:04:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260876"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260876"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12535"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17475143","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17475143"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T22:29:33+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T22:29:33+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12535"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1260876","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1260876"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T05:01:27+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T05:06:08+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"new","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":1,"questionsAnswered":1,"marksTotal":1,"marksAttainable":1,"marksAttempted":1,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T05:04:08+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"12535","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12535"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.52,0.06,0.17,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5034"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103663"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5034","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5034"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12535"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86080"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"9"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"82"},{"type":"tags","id":"9735"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"10061"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31289"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34402"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34857"},{"type":"contributions","id":"36585"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49638"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103663","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/103663"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 8-year-old boy presents to the emergency department with his teacher. He has a history of supraventricular tachycardia. He was sent in by school nurse after he complained of palpitations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHe is reviewed in the resuscitation room. He is alert, interactive and in no distress. His pulse rate is 210/min, blood pressure 110/70mmHg, and capillary refill time is 2 seconds.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Administer oral propanolol","Trial handstand with adult supervision","Prepare for electrocardioversion","Place a large bore cannula in the peripheral vein","Call the cardiologist for an urgent echocardiogram"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has presented in supraventricular tachycardia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf pulses were not palpable, or any clinical concerns for shock (poor perfusion, hypotension, altered mental state), then the pulseless cardiac arrest APLS protocol should be followed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, where he is alert, pulses are palpable and he has adequate perfusion then the next best steps would be:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Col\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBasic life support: airway, breathing, circulation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAttach cardiac monitoring and defibrillation pads, obtain ECG\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAttempt \u003Cstrong\u003Evagal stimulation\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EObtain IV access for \u003Cstrong\u003Eadenosine\u003C/strong\u003E (up to 3 doses may be trialled)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EConsider \u003Cstrong\u003Esynchronised DC cardioversion \u003C/strong\u003Eif failure of medical management\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ol\u003E\u003Cp\u003EValsalva manoeuvres are safe, minimally invasive, and generally effective for reverting supraventricular tachycardia in a haemodynamically stable patient. In this scenario, it appears reasonable to attempt simple vagal manoeuvres whilst obtaining equipment for vascular access. If unsuccessful, or clinical deterioration, proceed to medical treatment as per the algorithm. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOptions for vagal stimulation depend on the age of the child, and include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIce to face (5 second face submersion in icy water for infant)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EValsalva technique by blowing into closed syringe or narrow straw\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EModified Valsalva as above in semi-recumbent position then at end of the strain immediately repositioning into a supine position with passive leg raise to 45 degrees\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHandstand with adult assistance if child well enough\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOral \u003Cstrong\u003Epropanolol\u003C/strong\u003E is a beta blocker which can be used however is not first line, and adenosine would be preferred in the first instance.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere is no clear role or indication for \u003Cstrong\u003Eechocardiogram\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Always remember to follow a logical resuscitation algorithm in an acutely deteriorating patient.","Vagal stimulation is often effective in managing supraventricular tachycardia in the paediatric population."],"references":["Kliegman, Robert. Nelson Textbook of Pediatrics. Edition 21. Philadelphia, PA: Elsevier, 2020","The Royal Children\u0027s Hospital Melbourne. Clinical Practice Guidelines : Supraventricular Tachycardia SVT [Internet]. Royal Children\u0027s Hospital. 2019. Available from: https://www.rch.org.au/clinicalguide/guideline_index/Supraventricular_Tachycardia_SVT/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86080"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12535"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86080","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86080"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-25T15:15:09+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-25T15:15:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5034"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"103663"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"descripti